## Accent Colors *(reserved for future SKUs)*

| Name | Hex | Intended future use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Algae | `#1D7A6B` | SKU 03 reserve — honey, matcha, or earthy flavor direction |
| Feral | `#D94F6A` | SKU 04 reserve — strawberry, spicy, or bold flavor direction |

## Color System Logic

- **Fixed across all SKUs:** Roast (wordmark) + Cream (label bg) — these never change
- **Changes per SKU:** Accent stripe (top) · wave divider stroke · footer wave fill · flavor pill background
- **Rust is always visible:** The wordmark on every SKU uses Rust, giving cross-SKU brand recognition even when the accent color shifts
- **Shelf recognition rule:** A shopper identifies any Spoonless SKU by cream label + roast wordmark before reading a word. Accent color signals flavor, not a different brand.

## Color Groups

- **Structural pair (never changes):** Roast + Cream
- **Primary brand accent:** Rust + Ember
- **SKU 02 accent:** Golden + Dark Choc (#4A2C14)
- **Future SKU reserves:** Algae + Feral

