# 02b · Label System — SKU Flavor Architecture

*One label system. Infinite flavors. Zero redesigns.*

## Fixed Elements (all SKUs)

- Label background: Cream `#F5EDD8`
- Brand wordmark: "SPOONLESS" in DM Sans 500 · color: Rust `#E8622A`
- Product name hero: "peanut butter drizzle" in DM Serif Display · Roast base, italic "drizzle" in accent
- Wave divider: SVG wavy line — stroke color changes per SKU
- Flavor pill: positioned below wave — background + label text change per SKU
- Tagline / descriptor: 1–2 lines in DM Serif Display italic · copy changes per SKU
- Footer wave shape: arc fill — color changes per SKU
- Size / info line: DM Sans Light 300 · Cream text on colored footer

## Per-SKU Variables

| SKU | Flavor | Stripe color | Wave + footer | Pill bg | Descriptor |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 01 | Original | Rust `#E8622A` | Rust `#E8622A` | Roast `#1C1410` | *squeeze. drizzle. repeat.* |
| 02 | Chocolate Hazelnut | Golden `#E8A020` | Golden `#E8A020` | Dark Choc `#4A2C14` | *dark, rich, a little dangerous.* |
| 03+ | TBD | Algae or Feral | Matches stripe | Deep tone of stripe color | TBD at launch |

> **Important:** "peanut butter drizzle" is the fixed product name on every SKU. Flavor identity lives only in the flavor pill (e.g. "Chocolate · Hazelnut", "Original"). The hero typography does not change between SKUs.
