# 06 · Copy by Persona

*Same product. Three different doors.*

## The Ritual Optimizer *(TikTok / DTC)*

- Core tension: indulgence vs. performance
- Ad tone: clinical-cool, proof-forward
- Best lines:
    - *"No jar. No knife. No negotiating with the lid."*
    - *"Peanut butter, optimized."*
    - *"The only thing we added was the squeeze top."*
    - *"Two ingredients. One squeeze. Every morning."*

## The Considered Indulger *(Instagram / Specialty Retail)*

- Core tension: pleasure vs. integrity
- Ad tone: sensory, playful, zero health preaching
- Best lines:
    - *"Finally, peanut butter that knows it's a topping."*
    - *"It's not health food. It's just really good peanut butter."*
    - *"For people who take Sunday mornings seriously."*
    - *"Your waffle called. It wants this."*

## The Standard-Keeper *(Amazon / Instacart)*

- Core tension: speed vs. quality
- Ad tone: utility-forward, zero condescension
- Best lines:
    - *"Lunch boxes, smoothies, waffles. One squeeze."*
    - *"No more sticky lids. No more knives in the sink."*
    - *"Clean label. Zero mess. Every morning."*
    - *"Subscribe and never think about it again."*

## Universal (any channel)

> *"Peanut butter, optimized."*
> 

